{"ts":"2026-06-26T23:36:00.293Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"run_commands","toolCallId":"gslt0mxl","output":[{"query":"grep -n '\"60' automation/tasks.json || true","result":"483:    \"id\": \"60-phase3-tool-empty-loading-error-states\",\n","success":true},{"query":"grep -C 10 \"empty\" automation/tasks.json || true","result":"    \"target\": \"whole project\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform a preflight audit only. Do not edit files. Inspect package.json, app route tree, app/page.tsx, components/LandingPage.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/sections, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/landing-data.ts, lib/blueprint-data.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, and components/CommandCenter.tsx if they exist. Confirm the framework, routing model, styling stack, animation libraries, current page architecture, and whether framer-motion or motion/react is installed. Confirm whether any Aceternity UI components already exist; do not install anything. Check that there is no app/[...slug]/page.tsx and no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx. Search for PublicRoutePage imports and slug catch-all references. Check whether the landing page has all required homepage sections: Hero, Enterprise Quick Search, Garage Foundry Factory journey, What We Build, Interactive Experience, Global Presence, Client Success, Live Dashboard, Latest Research, Contact, Footer. Check whether all public pages are explicit App Router pages. Check whether the Blueprint scoring formula exists and whether the banking test case can return 87/100. Produce a gap list only. Do not edit files. Final response must include files inspected, missing items, route gaps, homepage gaps, design-system observations, animation-library availability, and recommended next task.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"01-safety-cleanup-no-slug-no-publicroutepage\",\n    \"title\": \"Remove forbidden slug route leftovers\",\n    \"scope\": \"routing-safety\",\n    \"target\": \"explicit public route architecture\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Implement only routing safety cleanup. Remove any forbidden catch-all slug route leftovers. There must be no app/[...slug]/page.tsx, no empty app/[...slug] directory, no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx, and no imports or references to PublicRoutePage. Do not redesign anything. Do not touch the landing page. Ensure all public pages remain explicit App Router pages. If an explicit page is missing, create a minimal explicit page file that uses the existing shared inner-page template, not slug logic. Run lint and build. Acceptance: no module-not-found for PublicRoutePage, no slug route files, no slug references, build passes, landing page unchanged.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"02-global-design-system-for-inner-pages\",\n    \"title\": \"Create premium inner-page design primitives\",\n    \"scope\": \"design-system\",\n    \"target\": \"public pages except landing\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or improve shared design primitives for all public inner pages except the landing page. Do not modify app/page.tsx, components/LandingPage.tsx, or existing landing sections. Inspect the landing page visual language and create inner-page-only components that follow its theme while allowing unique page designs. Build lightweight, maintainable components such as InnerPageShell, InnerPageHero, NarrativeSection, PremiumCTA, MotionReveal, BentoGrid, RelatedPagesGrid, ArchitectureDiagram, OperatingModelTimeline, EnterpriseFlowDiagram, AnimatedBackgroundGrid, PlatformProductPreview, IndustrySolutionMap, ResearchLibraryGrid, GlobalHubMap, SecurePortalPreview, and Carousel if useful. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Use Aceternity-inspired patterns such as bento grids, spotlight backgrounds, moving borders, sticky reveals, timelines, and card stacks by implementing lightweight local components with current Tailwind/CSS, not by installing heavy dependencies. Add SVG/CSS graphics and abstract visual panels. No external image URLs, no copyrighted images, no fake screenshots, no fake client logos. All components must be responsive, accessible, respect reduced motion, and scoped so they do not alter the landing page. Run lint/build. Final response must confirm landing page untouched.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n    \"target\": \"landing hero\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Inspect the landing hero only. Preserve the approved hero UI exactly, especially the right-side video placement, hero layout, spacing, typography, video container, overlay, and responsive behavior. Do not redesign the hero. Verify the hero contains the required headline: Building the World's First AI-Native Enterprise Transformation Company. Verify the subheading: Combining Agentic AI, Knowledge Graphs, Industry Platforms, Talent Cloud, and Managed AI Operations into a single transformation ecosystem. Verify primary CTA: Generate My Enterprise AI Blueprint. Verify secondary CTA: Experience GFF AI Live. Add or preserve hero metrics in the least intrusive existing style: 500+ AI Use Cases, 20+ Industries, Global Delivery Model, Agent Factory, Knowledge Graph Factory, AI Academy. Do not create fake metrics. Do not replace the video with a dashboard or foundry visual. Run lint/build. Final response must confirm hero video placement untouched.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"04-homepage-enterprise-quick-search\",\n    \"title\": \"Restore or build Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Enterprise Quick Search after hero\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add or restore Section 2 Enterprise Quick Search immediately after the approved hero. This section is mandatory. Preserve the approved hero and all existing landing styles. Build a local, frontend-only AI concierge style search that searches static local content across Industries, Capabilities, Platforms, Build With GFF tools, Resources, and Company pages. Include clickable example searches: Build AI for Banking, Create University AI Lab, Insurance AI, Mining AI, Retail AI, Build AI GCC. Results must appear instantly when typing or clicking examples. Each result must show title, category, short description, and route link. No API calls. No backend. No fake data. Design must be premium, clean, Apple-like, and consistent with the current landing theme. Use subtle Framer Motion or CSS transitions if available. Avoid box-inside-box clutter, excessive pills, badge soup, and neon overload. Mobile must be excellent. Acceptance: section appears after hero, search works locally, examples work, empty state is polished, links resolve, build passes.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"05-homepage-garage-foundry-factory-journey\",\n    \"title\": \"Complete Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n    \"scope\": \"homepage-section\",\n    \"target\": \"Garage Foundry Factory journey\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": true,\n    \"prompt\": \"Verify or restore the homepage transformation journey. It must include Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, Optimize, and Scale. Use the existing approved landing section if one already maps to this. Do not create duplicates. Do not redesign approved sections unnecessarily. Each step should have a concise description, outcome, and route link: Garage /platforms/garage, Foundry /platforms/foundry, Factory /platforms/factory, Operate /capabilities/operations or /platforms/control-center, Optimize /platforms/control-center, Scale /platforms/factory. UI should feel premium, like an enterprise operating model timeline, with subtle motion and responsive vertical mobile layout. Avoid visual clutter. Run lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n    \"target\": \"shared interactive tool foundation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build the shared frontend-only architecture for Phase 3 interactive tools. Do not touch the landing page. Do not add backend/API/AWS/auth/OTP/email/database/export integrations. Create or improve lightweight shared utilities and components needed by /build tools. The goal is to make every Build With GFF tool feel consistent, premium, and product-grade while keeping each tool unique. Inspect existing components and avoid duplicate systems. Create only necessary files. Suggested elements: ToolPageShell, ToolHero, ToolStepLayout, ToolSidebarProgress, ToolResultPanel, ToolInputGroup, ToolOptionGrid, ToolSummaryCard, ToolEmptyState, ToolPreviewNotice, ToolCTA, ToolMotionReveal, ToolTabs, ToolCarousel, ToolComparisonRail, and ToolDataCard if useful. Create shared TypeScript types for industry, company size, AI journey, data readiness, priorities, assessment answers, ROI inputs, proposal inputs, sandbox agent, marketplace agent, and generated local reports. Create local-only service helpers inside an existing placeholder/service file or a new small lib file if needed. Do not create network calls. Do not create fake real outputs. Use deterministic local calculations and clearly labelled previews. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Use Aceternity-inspired patterns locally, such as bento grids, moving borders, spotlight cards, tabs, and card stacks, but do not install heavy dependencies. All components must be responsive, accessible, and visually aligned with the approved landing page theme. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"40-phase3-shared-data-models-and-validation\",\n    \"title\": \"Create shared data models validation and constants\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-foundation\",\n    \"target\": \"tool data models and validation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or improve shared frontend-only data models, constants, and validation utilities for Phase 3 tools. Do not touch the landing page. Do not add backend calls. Centralize reusable data so tools do not hardcode repeated arrays. Include industries: Banking, Healthcare, Manufacturing, Retail, Education, Government, Insurance, Financial Services, Life Sciences, Mining, Energy, Telecom, Audit, Tax, Legal, Advisory, Other. Include company sizes: <100, 100-1000, 1000-10000, 10000+. Include AI journeys: No AI, Exploring AI, Running Pilots, Scaling AI, AI-Driven Enterprise, AI-Native. Include priorities: Reduce Costs, Increase Revenue, Improve Productivity, Improve Customer Experience, Automate Processes, Strengthen Compliance, AI Transformation. Include data readiness levels and leadership commitment levels exactly as required by the Blueprint scoring. Include reusable validation helpers: required text, email format, max selected priorities, number ranges, non-negative currency/volume inputs, safe empty states. Include common suggested AI opportunities: Procurement Copilot, HR Assistant, Contract Intelligence, Knowledge Search, Executive Dashboard, Compliance Assistant, Customer Experience Agent, Document Intelligence Agent, Operations Copilot. Include GFF solution recommendations: Agent Factory, Knowledge Graph, AI Governance, Managed AI Operations, Garage, Foundry, Factory, Control Center. All helpers must be local and deterministic. Add unit-style pure functions where sensible, but do not introduce a test framework unless already present. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"41-phase3-reusable-wizard-and-stepper\",\n    \"title\": \"Build reusable premium wizard and stepper system\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-component\",\n    \"target\": \"wizard and stepper UI\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build a reusable wizard/stepper system for Build With GFF tools. Do not touch landing page. The system should support multi-step flows for Blueprint, Assessment, ROI, Proposal, and Talk to Agent. It must support step labels, progress, back/next actions, keyboard accessibility, validation messages, mobile stacking, summary side panel, result state, and local-only reset. Design must be premium and custom, not generic form UI. Use current site theme, tasteful motion, clear hierarchy, and mobile-friendly interactions. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed for step transitions and progress animations. Respect prefers-reduced-motion. Avoid excessive pills, nested boxes, and badge clutter. Do not add backend calls. Do not change actual page content yet except where needed to wire the reusable system into existing tool pages if safe. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"59-phase3-command-center-deep-actions\",\n    \"title\": \"Enhance Command Center with Build tool deep actions\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-navigation\",\n    \"target\": \"Command Center\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Enhance the Command Center with Build With GFF deep actions. Do not touch landing page. Existing Cmd+K/Ctrl+K behavior must remain. Add commands for Start Blueprint, Continue Blueprint if local state exists, Start Assessment, Estimate ROI, Build Proposal, Open Sandbox, Compare Agents, Open Foundry Studio, Clear Local Workspace, Contact Sales, Book Workshop. Keep it frontend-only. Use route navigation and local actions only. Ensure keyboard accessibility, focus trap if modal, escape close, mobile fallback button if needed, and visible focus states. Do not redesign global header unless required. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"60-phase3-tool-empty-loading-error-states\",\n    \"title\": \"Polish empty loading error and completion states\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-ux-polish\",\n    \"target\": \"all Build tools\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Polish empty states, loading-like transitions, error states, validation states, completion states, and reset states across all Build With GFF tools. Do not touch landing page. Tools: /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Since everything is frontend-only, use short deterministic transitions only where tasteful. Empty states must explain what the user should do. Validation states must be clear and accessible. Completion states must include next actions. Error states must not be scary or fake backend errors. Use premium microcopy and consistent visuals. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"61-phase3-mobile-pass-build-tools\",\n    \"title\": \"Mobile UX pass for Build With GFF tools\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-mobile-qa\",\n    \"target\": \"Build tool pages\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform a mobile UX pass for all Build With GFF tools. Do not redesign and do not touch landing page. Check /build, /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Fix only mobile and responsive issues. Ensure no horizontal overflow, readable text, easy form inputs, large tap targets, stepper usability, accessible carousels/tabs, stacked result panels, simplified diagrams, usable comparison drawer, and workflow builder fallback. Do not add new features. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n    \"target\": \"tool calculation logic\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Add lightweight verification for deterministic tool logic without introducing a heavy testing stack. Do not touch landing page. If an existing test framework exists, add small tests for Blueprint scoring, Assessment scoring, ROI calculation, local recommendation logic, and validation helpers. If no test framework exists, add a small documented npm-safe verification script only if consistent with the project, or add pure-function self-check comments/docs instead. The Banking Blueprint example must be covered: Banking, 10000+ company size, Scaling AI, Productivity + Cost Reduction + Compliance, Mostly Integrated Data, Budget Approved returns 87/100. Do not add dependencies unless absolutely necessary. Run available test command if present, then lint/build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"66-phase3-api-contract-documentation-only\",\n    \"title\": \"Document future FastAPI contracts for Phase 4\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-docs\",\n    \"target\": \"future backend API contract documentation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update documentation for future FastAPI backend contracts only. Do not build backend. Do not add FastAPI folder yet unless already present and explicitly documented as empty placeholder. Do not add API calls. Create docs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md or update existing docs. Document what Phase 3 built, what remains frontend-only, and future endpoints for Phase 4 or backend phase: POST /api/blueprint/generate, POST /api/assessment/score, POST /api/roi/calculate, POST /api/contact/submit, POST /api/proposal/generate, POST /api/auth/request-otp, POST /api/auth/verify-otp, POST /api/newsletter/subscribe, POST /api/sandbox/run, POST /api/foundry/workflow, GET /api/marketplace/agents. Document payload shapes at a high level, response examples clearly marked illustrative, security requirements, auth/session later, email/OTP provider later, database later, object storage later, and no AWS credentials in this phase. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"67-phase3-linking-and-cta-integration\",\n    \"title\": \"Integrate links and CTAs across Phase 3 tools\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-integration\",\n    \"target\": \"links CTAs navigation between tools\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Audit and improve internal linking between Build With GFF tools and related public pages. Do not touch landing page. Ensure /build links to every tool. Each tool should link to the next logical tools. Blueprint links to Assessment, ROI, Proposal, Talk. Assessment links to Blueprint and Talk. ROI links to Proposal and Blueprint. Proposal links to Talk and Contact. Sandbox links to Marketplace and Foundry Studio. Marketplace links to Sandbox and Proposal. Foundry Studio links to Proposal and Talk. Add related links to relevant Capabilities and Platforms where useful. No broken links. No slug links. Use existing CTA style. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"68-phase3-final-interactive-tools-qa\",\n    \"title\": \"Final Phase 3 QA for interactive tools\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase3-final-qa\",\n    \"target\": \"entire Phase 3 interactive layer\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for Phase 3 interactive Build With GFF tools. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify /build, /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Verify shared tool architecture works. Verify frontend-only safety: no backend, no AWS, no auth, no real OTP, no real email, no database, no real API calls, no real exports. Verify Blueprint scoring and Banking example 87/100. Verify assessment and ROI calculations are deterministic and labelled illustrative. Verify local workspace does not break hydration. Verify mobile responsiveness, accessibility, reduced motion, command center deep actions, links, CTAs, empty states, error states, result states, and visual polish. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, and TODOs for the next backend/FastAPI phase.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"69-phase4-preflight-portal-admin-audit\",\n    \"title\": \"Phase 4 preflight audit for login admin and client portal\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-audit\",\n    \"target\": \"login admin client portal frontend\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"This is the first task of Phase 4. Do not edit files. Audit the current implementation for all login, client portal, admin portal, and private workspace related routes and components. Inspect app/portal, app/client, app/admin if present, app/login if present, app/layout.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/CommandCenter.tsx, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, and any existing dashboard, portal, auth, client, admin, table, document, billing, support, analytics, or governance components. Determine what currently exists as a public shell and what is missing for a proper logged-in product experience. Do not create backend, real auth, database, AWS, email, OTP, payment, upload, or API integrations. Produce a detailed implementation gap report for Phase 4 frontend. The report must cover required routes, app shell, local auth preview, role switching, route protection preview, client portal dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, admin dashboard, client management, user management, project management, documents admin, billing admin, support admin, analytics admin, governance admin, activity feed, notifications, global search, command center, tables, filters, mobile UX, accessibility, design system, and final QA. Final response must include files inspected, existing capabilities, missing routes, missing components, design risks, and recommended implementation order. Do not edit files.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n    \"target\": \"local mock data\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create a local mock data model for the client portal and admin portal. Do not add a database or backend. Do not create fake real customer data that implies actual clients. Use clearly representative data and label it as preview/demo data where surfaced. Data should support dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing/invoices, support tickets, analytics, governance, users, clients, activity feed, and notifications. Include types for ClientAccount, Project, Program, AgentOperation, AgentHealth, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, AnalyticsMetric, GovernanceItem, Approval, User, Role, ActivityEvent, Notification. Include deterministic sample entries such as representative client account, representative project names, representative agent names, preview invoices, preview tickets. No fake logos or real client names. Centralize in a safe local data file. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"78-phase4-data-table-filter-system\",\n    \"title\": \"Build premium data table filter and list system\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-component\",\n    \"target\": \"tables lists filters\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build reusable premium table, list, filter, and detail-drawer components for portal and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. Components should support search, status filters, type filters, date range placeholder, sort controls, empty state, row click, selected state, pagination or local visible count, mobile card fallback, and accessible keyboard navigation. Use these components for Projects, Documents, Billing, Support, Users, Clients, AI Operations, Governance, and Activity. Make the design feel custom and expensive, not default HTML tables. Use subtle row hover, sticky header where useful, and clean responsive cards on mobile. No backend calls. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"79-phase4-client-dashboard\",\n    \"title\": \"Build Client Portal Dashboard\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-client-portal\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/dashboard\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build /portal/dashboard as the main client portal cockpit. Do not touch landing page. Use the private app shell. The dashboard should include welcome header, account summary, active projects, AI operations status, document updates, billing snapshot, open support tickets, analytics highlights, governance alerts, recent activity, and next actions. Use representative preview data only, no fake live data. Dashboard widgets should be visually premium, with bento layout, metric tiles, progress visuals, status cards, timeline, and CTA cards. Metrics must be clearly preview/demo if they could be mistaken as real. Add links to Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance. Mobile must stack beautifully. Use motion lightly. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"80-phase4-client-projects-list\",\n    \"title\": \"Build Client Portal Projects list\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-client-portal\",\n    \"target\": \"/portal/projects\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build /portal/projects as a premium project and program management view for clients. Do not touch landing page. Include project cards or table with search, status filters, phase filters such as Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, owner, timeline, progress, next milestone, and health status. Use representative preview data only. Include empty state and local detail drawer if dynamic route is not used. UI should feel like a high-end enterprise delivery dashboard. Add CTA to request update or contact support using frontend-only action. No backend. Mobile card view required. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"81-phase4-client-project-detail\",\n    \"title\": \"Build Client Portal Project detail experience\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-client-portal\",\n    \"target\": \"project detail\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build the client project detail experience using /portal/projects/[id] if the current route architecture supports it, otherwise use a detail drawer from /portal/projects. Do not touch landing page. Project detail must include overview, project phase, scope, timeline, milestones, squad, deliverables, linked documents, approvals, support items, AI operations connected to the project, recent activity, and next steps. Include tabs: Overview, Timeline, Deliverables, Team, Documents, Activity. Use representative preview data only. Make it polished, narrative, and operational with timeline visuals and progress indicators. No API calls. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n    \"target\": \"/admin/activity\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build /admin/activity as internal operational activity feed. Do not touch landing page. Include events across clients, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, governance, users, and settings. Add filters by module, client, actor, severity, and date range preview. Use representative local data only. No real audit logs. Clearly label as preview. Design should feel like a premium audit/activity timeline with detail drawer. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"108-phase4-global-private-search\",\n    \"title\": \"Build global private workspace search\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-navigation\",\n    \"target\": \"private search\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build a local global search for private workspace pages. Do not touch landing page. The search should be available from the private topbar and/or command center. It must search local preview data across projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support tickets, governance items, clients, users, and admin pages depending on role. No API calls. Results should show type, title, description, status, and route or action. Include keyboard navigation, empty state, and mobile support. Design must feel like a premium enterprise search palette. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"109-phase4-private-command-center\",\n    \"title\": \"Enhance command center for client and admin workspaces\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-navigation\",\n    \"target\": \"private command center\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Enhance the command center for logged-in preview workspaces. Do not touch landing page. Existing public command center behavior must not break. Add client commands: Open Dashboard, Open Projects, Open AI Operations, Open Documents, Open Billing, Open Support, Open Analytics, Open Governance, Open Settings, Create Support Ticket Preview, Clear Local Session. Add admin commands: Open Admin Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings, Activity. Commands must be role-aware using local preview session. Keyboard accessible, escape close, focus handling, mobile fallback. No backend. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"110-phase4-notifications-system\",\n    \"title\": \"Build frontend-only notifications system\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-component\",\n    \"target\": \"notifications\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build a frontend-only notifications system for private workspace. Do not touch landing page. Add notification bell in private topbar if not already present. Notifications should come from local representative data: project update, document shared, invoice status, support reply, AI operation review, governance approval. Support mark-read locally and link to related page. No push notifications, no email, no backend. Design should be polished, with dropdown panel, empty state, mobile support, and accessible keyboard behavior. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"111-phase4-approvals-and-tasks-preview\",\n    \"title\": \"Build approvals and tasks preview system\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-component\",\n    \"target\": \"approvals and tasks\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Build a local approvals and tasks preview system shared across client and admin portals. Do not touch landing page. Approval types: document approval, governance review, project milestone approval, invoice review, AI operation human review. Client users can see their approvals in portal dashboard and governance. Admin users can see all approvals in admin dashboard and governance. Actions such as approve, request changes, mark reviewed must be local preview only and clearly not backend. Add polished approval cards, filters, and detail drawer. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"112-phase4-private-empty-states\",\n    \"title\": \"Polish private app empty states and locked states\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-ux-polish\",\n    \"target\": \"empty locked states\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Polish empty states, locked states, unauthenticated states, no-results states, and preview-only notices across login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Every empty state should explain what it means and what action is available. Locked states should be role-aware and explain permissions preview. Unauthenticated routes should show a premium sign-in required state with route to /portal/login. No scary errors. No fake backend failure. Use polished graphics and microcopy. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"113-phase4-route-guard-ux\",\n    \"title\": \"Improve route guard and role access UX\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-auth-preview\",\n    \"target\": \"route guards\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Improve frontend-only route guard UX for client and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. If no local preview session exists, private routes should show sign-in required or redirect safely to /portal/login depending on current app pattern. If a user has a client role and opens /admin, show access restricted preview. If an admin role opens /portal pages, allow or show switch workspace depending on chosen preview logic. Add clear role preview switcher and sign out action. Do not implement real security. Do not use backend. Ensure hydration safety. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n    \"target\": \"private workspace motion\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform motion and interaction polish for login, portal, and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Add subtle page transitions, sidebar active motion, card reveal, table row hover, drawer transitions, notification dropdown animation, command palette transitions, chart reveal, status card micro-interactions, and form state transitions where appropriate. Respect prefers-reduced-motion. Keep motion expensive and calm, not noisy. Do not add dependencies. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"117-phase4-premium-visual-polish-private-workspace\",\n    \"title\": \"Premium visual polish for private workspace\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-visual-polish\",\n    \"target\": \"login portal admin UI\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform final premium visual polish for login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Improve any UI that feels generic, unfinished, repetitive, too boxy, too badge-heavy, or like a basic admin template. Make the private workspace feel like a custom 2026 enterprise AI operations product built by a senior design team. Use refined spacing, typography, bento dashboards, high-quality tables, elegant filters, strong empty states, premium charts, SVG/CSS visual panels, subtle gradients, and purposeful motion. Do not add fake data. Do not add dependencies. Preserve public site theme. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"118-phase4-frontend-only-safety-audit\",\n    \"title\": \"Frontend-only safety audit for Phase 4\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-safety\",\n    \"target\": \"auth portal admin safety\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Audit and fix frontend-only safety for Phase 4. Do not touch landing page. Search for fetch, axios, app/api usage, localhost API calls, auth providers, JWT verification, Cognito, Firebase, Supabase, Clerk, AWS, S3, SES, payment providers, upload APIs, email sending, OTP sending, database imports, real file downloads, real invoice generation, and server actions. Remove or disable any accidental real integration in login, portal, admin, documents, billing, support, and analytics. All auth/session/data must be local preview only. If legacy app/api/contact exists, do not use it from Phase 4 UI. Run lint and build.\"\n  },\n  {\n--\n    \"target\": \"Phase 4 documentation\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Create or update documentation for Phase 4 frontend implementation. Do not build backend. Create docs/PHASE_4_LOGIN_ADMIN_CLIENT_PORTAL.md or update existing docs. Document routes built, local auth preview behavior, roles, route guard preview, client portal modules, admin modules, local mock data, frontend-only limitations, future backend requirements, future FastAPI endpoints, future database tables, future storage needs, future email/OTP needs, future billing/payment integration, and security considerations. Clearly state that Phase 4 is frontend-only and not production authentication. Include recommended Phase 5 backend build order. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"121-phase4-final-qa\",\n    \"title\": \"Final Phase 4 QA\",\n    \"scope\": \"phase4-final-qa\",\n    \"target\": \"login admin client portal frontend\",\n    \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n    \"prompt\": \"Perform final QA for Phase 4. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify /portal is a Client Login landing and contains module previews for Dashboard, Projects, Invoices or Billing, Support, Documents, AI Operations, Analytics, Governance. Verify /login and /portal/login work as frontend-only local preview login. Verify local roles and route guards work as previews. Verify client portal pages: Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings, Activity. Verify admin pages: Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings, Activity. Verify private shell, sidebar, topbar, notifications, command center, global search, tables, filters, detail drawers, local data, empty states, locked states, mobile, accessibility, and visual polish. Verify no backend, real auth, AWS, OTP, email, database, uploads, payments, or real API calls were added. Verify no landing page files were changed. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, and TODOs for Phase 5 backend.\"\n  }\n]\n","success":true}],"durationMs":13}}
